flashrom
Utility for flash chip reading/writing

Hardware Hacking
Description
flashrom is a utility for identifying, reading, writing, verifying and erasing flash chips. Used for firmware extraction and modification.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which flashrom
Install command:

sudo apt install flashrom
Basic Syntax
flashrom [options]
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
flashrom -p internal

Detect internal chip	Check BIOS chip	
flashrom -p internal -r backup.bin

Read firmware	Backup BIOS	
flashrom -p internal -w firmware.bin

Write firmware	Flash new BIOS	
flashrom -p ch341a_spi

Use CH341A programmer	External flash read	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Identify flash chip
2
Backup original firmware
3
Modify or prepare new firmware
4
Write to chip
5
Verify write
Understanding the Output
Shows chip detection, read/write progress, and verification status.

Important Warnings
•
Can brick devices if done wrong
•
Backup before writing
•
Only modify authorized hardware
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
